This paper discusses the properties of different consensus mechanisms in cryptocurrencies, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves simulations and measurements, which could be considered as aspects of distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the concept of egalitarianism in cryptocurrencies, which could be related to the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CY), game theory (cs.GT), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
